## Assertion Reference

Each `assertion` block has the shape `{ source, property, comparison, target }`. Which comparisons are allowed, and what `target` must contain, depend on `source`. The `comparison` and `target` rules are enforced by the Checkly API at apply time; where `property` is marked as ignored, the API accepts any value but does not use it.

| `source` | `property` | Allowed `comparison` values | `target` |
|---|---|---|---|
| `RESPONSE_TIME` | Leave empty (ignored for this source). | `EQUALS`, `NOT_EQUALS`, `GREATER_THAN`, `LESS_THAN` | Milliseconds, ≥ 0. |
| `GRPC_STATUS_CODE` | Leave empty (ignored for this source). | `EQUALS`, `NOT_EQUALS`, `GREATER_THAN`, `LESS_THAN` | Integer 0–16 (standard gRPC status codes; `0` = OK). |
| `GRPC_HEALTHCHECK_STATUS` | Leave empty (ignored for this source). | `EQUALS`, `NOT_EQUALS` | Integer 0–3: `0` = UNKNOWN, `1` = SERVING, `2` = NOT_SERVING, `3` = SERVICE_UNKNOWN. Numeric only — labels are not accepted. |
| `GRPC_RESPONSE` | A JSONPath expression into the response message (e.g. `$.user.id`). | `EQUALS`, `NOT_EQUALS`, `HAS_KEY`, `NOT_HAS_KEY`, `HAS_VALUE`, `NOT_HAS_VALUE`, `IS_EMPTY`, `NOT_EMPTY`, `GREATER_THAN`, `LESS_THAN`, `CONTAINS`, `NOT_CONTAINS`, `IS_NULL`, `NOT_NULL` | Free-form string. |
| `TEXT_BODY` | Optional; selects within the serialized response body. | Same set as `GRPC_RESPONSE`. | Free-form string. |
| `GRPC_METADATA` | A response metadata (header) key. | Same set as `GRPC_RESPONSE`. | Free-form string. |

### Examples

```terraform
# The unary call must return gRPC status OK.
assertion {
  source     = "GRPC_STATUS_CODE"
  comparison = "EQUALS"
  target     = "0"
}

# HEALTH mode: the service must report SERVING (numeric target).
assertion {
  source     = "GRPC_HEALTHCHECK_STATUS"
  comparison = "EQUALS"
  target     = "1"
}

# A field selected from the response message via JSONPath.
assertion {
  source     = "GRPC_RESPONSE"
  property   = "$.user.id"
  comparison = "NOT_NULL"
}

# A response metadata (header) value.
assertion {
  source     = "GRPC_METADATA"
  property   = "x-request-id"
  comparison = "NOT_EMPTY"
}
```
